Granted the  wand is a very nice stat item .. but when it comes to the sheer performance of the pets, was wondering if my efforts were better to just level and get 61 pet? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyphyr>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 760<br> <font color=#333333>(12/29/02 4:20:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is epic pet obsolete with lvl 61 pet?</span><hr size=1> It isn't quite obsolete. It just isn't absolutely required to be the best a mage can be anymore.<br>
<br>
It tanks slightly better than the 61/62 pets. I don't know how its tanking compares to the 65 Earth though, since neither I nor anyone else I know has it yet (only 3 level 65 spells total in my guild so far and none are mage).<br>
<br>
The 61/62 do a bit more damage (overall) than the epic, primarily due to the fact that they are level 60.<br>
<br>
<br>
The above is simply my observations. Other peoples experiences may vary. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
