Rampage list is determined soley by the order in which you enter the hate list. Actual agro is irrelevant. Having hit the mob with a burst of flame at that same instant where you sent your pet would have put you at the same spot on the Rampage list. A Water pet would have had the same effect. Heck, a level 4 earth pet would have done exactly the same for you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fabbz>Fabbz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#333333>(1/2/03 9:36:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is epic pet obsolete with lvl 61 pet?</span><hr size=1> yep, you just need a good pause to let all the melees start hitting before you send your pet in.  keep in mind that your pet, being computer controlled, will usually get in range and start hitting faster than most players if you hit attack right when the other melees are called in as well.<br>
