<br>
After looking at the log file, I singled out a few individual fights from engaged to death.  Epic pet parsed out at 46.9 DPS.  Then I looked at the log file, the pet's Proc went off a ton of times.  So I edited the log file to remove the message:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Froglok zol knight is slashed by shards of elemental power. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
and I replaced it with:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> [Thu Jan 16 23:25:11 2003] Lasarer slashes froglok zol knight for 143 points of damage. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I did this so I could actually see the damage being done from the Procs.  His DPS went up from 46.9 to 94.57.<br>
<br>
Now about adding in the Damage Shield damage...<br>
The Froglok hit the pet 8 times, so that's 8*50=400 damage from the DS.  The fight lasted 21 seconds and the pet did 1986 with the procs converted to melee damage.  so...<br>
1986/21= 94.57<br>
add in DS...<br>
2386/21= 113.6<br>
<br>
Ok, so think about that.  113.5 DPS.  Tell me that's not freaking good and PoP pets own.<br>
<br>
What buffs and gear did pet have?  Well he had<br>
-2 sword of runes<br>
-Muzzle of Mardu<br>
-Burnout 3 (leg buff)<br>
that's it.<br>
<br>
Sure a 61 pet can stack up once you haste them both and DS him.  But not when you consider DS damage and Proc damage.<br>
<br>
Sure a 62 water pet can outdamage his melee.  But not his proc+DS.<br>
<br>
Now, also consider, if the mobs were level 60+ then his DPS would have severly dropped due to resists and less melee damage.  So a PoP pet WOULD have better results against a higiher mob.  But just understand well what epic pet CAN do.<br>
<br>
Like I said, it's situational. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eandori>Eandori</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 503<br> <font color=#333333>(1/18/03 11:39:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Did another Sebilis parse</span><hr size=1> Just ran another parse.  Here's what happened and what I did.<br>
<br>
I was in Sebilis again.  3 Frogs aggro'd onto me and somebody close to me.  The pet tanked all 3 nearly the whole time with some minor tanking by the 2nd person.  The split second one of the 3 died, the pet was on the next, so it was a back to back fight of 3 mobs with some damage shield going on the whole time.<br>
<br>
Over the course of that fight from first pet swing to final exp message, pet got 62.5 DPS<br>
<br>
Then I converted all the Procs to a slash hit for 143 again so the parser could count those in.  The DPS went up to 100.8 DPS.<br>
<br>
Finally, I added another slash hit to each of the mobs after every hit they did to my pet.  I added a 50 damage slash to account for the damage shield damage that was being done.  That took some time to edit, because I had to copy the time of the mob-hitting-pet event and paste it below with the added slash for 50.  That final DPS parsed out to 123.0<br>
<br>
So just melee...............= 62.5 DPS<br>
Melee + Proc................= 100.8 DPS<br>
Melee + Proc + DS........= 123.0 DPS<br>
<br>
Notes: <br>
-Epic pet with 2 sword of runes and Muzzle<br>
-Burnout 3 (leg buff)<br>
-Sebilis mobs near exit (level 45-47?)<br>
<br>
====================<br>
====MY CONCLUSION====<br>
====================<br>
<br>
No, Epic pet is not obsolete.  If you don't believe my parses, then go do this and see for yourself.   ;-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 315<br> <font color=#333333>(1/19/03 7:46:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Did another Sebilis parse</span><hr size=1> It would be interesting to see the Epic pet parsed with some Blades of Walnan as well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
