<br>
I read over the epic pet parses lots of times and often wondered if that damage included the proc's and DS.  When I actually started doing parsing on my own I quickly discovered they didn't.  I think there is alot of mages that WANT to believe epic is no longer the best.  I think they want to find a way to see themselves as either better then other mages, or better then they have been since getting epic.  So they are quick to dismiss epic's true usefullness.<br>
<br>
Only looking at epic pet's melee damage, and ignoring the Proc's and DS is idiotic in my opinion.  Was it the melee damage of the level 49 fire pet that made it a favorite for so many mages for so long?  HELL NO, it was that huge DS.  People could have just cast earth pet and DS'd it, but no, we all used the 49 fire because the DS ROCKED!<br>
<br>
Epic pet proc's go off ALOT.  Ignoring them for damage comparisons is foolish.  The only valid argument was for very high level mobs that epic could not land spells on. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
